kind": "italic_en", "text": "i. q."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aTaAqa", "text_ar": "اَطَاقَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He was able;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "he was able to do,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "accomplish,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "a thing, and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to acquire"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "obtain"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "it, and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to have"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "it, &c.]; (K, TA; [in the CK, erroneously,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aTaAEa", "text_ar": "اَطَاعَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", which, however, correctly explains one meaning of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AstTAE", "text_ar": "استطاع"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", as will be seen by what follows;]) the inf. n. being"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "syn. with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_iTaAqapN", "text_ar": "اـِطَاقَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, O, TA,) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TaAqapN", "text_ar": "طَاقَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Msb,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qudorapN", "text_ar": "قُدْرَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (Msb, TA:) but it is said peculiarly of a human being [or a rational creature], whereas"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ATAq", "text_ar": "اطاق"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is used in a general manner: (IB, TA:) and the application of the former requires a peculiar constitution of the agent, and the conception of the act, and the fitness of the object to be acted upon or effected, and the possession of an instrument when the action is instrumental as in the case of writing: (Er-Rághib, TA:) and one says also, (K,) or sometimes they said, (S, O, Msb,)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AisoTaAEa", "text_ar": "اِسْطَاعَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, O, Msb, K,) aor."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yasoTiyEu", "text_ar": "يَسْطِيعُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, O, Msb,) with fet-h [to the first letter]; (Msb;) rejecting the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "t", "text_ar": "ت"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", deeming it difficult of utterance with the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "T", "text_ar": "ط"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and disliking to incorporate it into the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "T", "text_ar": "ط"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "because the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "s", "text_ar": "س"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "would then become movent, which it never is: Hamzeh (i. e. Ez-Zeiyát, TA, not Khallád, O, K, TA) read, [in the Kur xviii. 96,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "famaA", "text_ar": "فَمَا"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A@soT~aAEuwA", "text_ar": "ا@سْطَّاعُوا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", with idghám, combining two quiescent letters: (S, O, K:) this reading is said by Zj, as on the authority of Kh and Yoo and Sb and others, to be incorrect; but Abu-l-'Abbás Ahmad Ibn Mohammad Ibn-'Abd-El-Ghanee Ed-Dimyátee, who died in the year [of the Flight] 1116, and Ibn-El-Jezeree, and El-Háfidh Aboo-'Amr, contradict him, affirming it to be allowable: (TA:) and Akh says, (S, O,) and some of the Arabs say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AisotaAEa", "text_ar": "اِسْتَاعَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", aor."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yasotiyEu", "text_ar": "يَسْتِيعُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, O, K,) rejecting the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "T", "text_ar": "ط"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (S, O;) which Zj holds to be not allowable in reading [the Kur-án]: (TA:) and some of the Arabs say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^asoTaAEa", "text_ar": "اَسْطَاعَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", aor."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yusoTiyEu", "text_ar": "يُسْطِيعُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", [in the CK, erroneously,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yasoTiyEu", "text_ar": "يَسْطِيعُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",] with the disjunctive"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A", "text_ar": "ا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[in the former], meaning"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aTaAEa", "text_ar": "اَطَاعَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", aor."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yuTiyEu", "text_ar": "يُطِيعُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Akh, S, O, K,) making the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "s", "text_ar": "س"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "to be a substitute for the suppressed vowel of the medial radical letter of the verb ["}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ATAE", "text_ar": "اطاع"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], (Akh, S, O,) for, as is said by Kh and Sb,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aTaAEa", "text_ar": "اَطَاعَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is originally"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aTowaEa", "text_ar": "اَطْوَعَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (TA;) or, as AZ says, the verb in this case, with damm to the aor., is likened to"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^afoEala", "text_ar": "اَفْعَلَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", aor."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yufoEilu", "text_ar": "يُفْعِلُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_ifoEaAlN", "text_ar": "اـِفْعَالٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (Msb:) but Zj says that he who reads"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "famaA A@saT~aAEuwA", "text_ar": "فَمَا ا@سَطَّاعُوا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "errs; for the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "s", "text_ar": "س"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AisotafoEala", "text_ar": "اِسْتَفْعَلَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is never movent: and Sb mentions"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA A^asotatiyEu", "text_ar": "مَا اَسْتَتِيعُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; holding it to be an instance of substitution. (TA.) ―         -b2-  See also 4. Some say that"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "halo yasotaTiyEu rab~uka A^ano yunaz~ila", "text_ar": "هَلْ يَسْتَطِيعُ رَبُّكَ اَنْ يُنَزِّلَ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EalayonaA maAy^idapF mina Als~amaA='i", "text_ar": "عَلَيْنَا مَايِدَةً مِنَ السَّمَا=ءِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in the Kur [v. 112], means"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "halo yujiybu", "text_ar": "هَلْ يُجِيبُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Will thy Lord consent,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "comply with the desire, that He should send down to us a table with food upon it from Heaven?"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (Er-Rághib, TA:) ―         -b3-  and Ks read"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "halo tasotaTiyEu rab~aka", "text_ar": "هَلْ تَسْتَطِيعُ رَبَّكَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Wilt thou demand of thy Lord that He consent,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "comply with the desire?"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(O, TA:) for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AstTAEhu", "text_ar": "استطاعهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He demanded his obedience,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "his consent,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "compliance with what he desired of him."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.)"}], "source_refs": ["S", "O", "Msb", "K", "B", "TA", "IB", "Akh"]}]}, "classical_definitions": {"source": "hawramani", "url": "https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%A7%D8%B3%D8%AA%D8%B7%D8%A7%D8%B9/", "headword_ar": "استطاعة", "entries": [{"lexicon_id": "dictionary_18", "lexicon_en": "Al-Sharīf al-Jurjānī, Kitāb al-Taʿrīfāt (d. 1413 CE)", "lexicon_ar": "كتاب التعريفات للشريف الجرجاني", "permalink": "https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=22825#faadae", "body_html": "<span>الاستطاعة: هي عرض يخلقه الله تعالى في الحيوان، يفعل به الأفعال الاختيارية.</span>"}, {"lexicon_id": "dictionary_18", "lexicon_en": "Al-Sharīf al-Jurjānī, Kitāb al-Taʿrīfāt (d. 1413 CE)", "lexicon_ar":